## Subgroup Profile

- Default profile: `dev-minimal` — planner + builder. Planner self-reviews while context is hot.
- Profile `dev-standard` (`planner + 2 builders + reviewer`): use for parallel work or higher-risk changes.
- Test group (`planner + patrol`): QA/evidence campaigns only; patrol does not edit product code.
- Validation: `local review/latest` is the operator validation snapshot. Planner merges accepted
  work to local `review/latest`. Memory/main only after operator authorization.
- No push, no PR, no CI unless operator explicitly requests it. CI opt-in.
- OpenClaw/Koder/Feishu/Lark are optional adapters — not required for normal subgroup work.
- Hot-plug rule: adding or removing a subgroup must not delete briefs, receipts, queue events, or memory facts.

## Gemini Notes

- Gemini does not rely on Claude Code Stop hooks. Always call
  `{{clawseat_root}}/core/skills/gstack-harness/scripts/complete_handoff.py`
  explicitly before notifying the next seat.
- Use `{{clawseat_root}}/core/shell-scripts/send-and-verify.sh --project {{project}}`
  for seat-to-seat protocol messages.
- Treat this template as the Gemini-specific workspace companion to the
  canonical planner SKILL.md.
